        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-10-03 18:36:14.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI have a single intermittent test failure in\nTestGenerateArtifactsServiceImpl.testGenerateArtifacts:54\n\nThe underlying cause is this exception:\n\nClassCastException: attempting to cast jar:file:/C:/Program%20Files/Java/jdk1.8.0_101/jre/lib/rt.jar!/javax/xml/bind/JAXBContext.class to jar:file:/C:/Program%20Files/Java/jdk1.8.0_101/jre/lib/rt.jar!/javax/xml/bind/JAXBContext.class.  Please make sure that you are specifying the proper ClassLoader.\n\nI can work around this by adding the parameter -DforkCount=1 to the Maven command that runs the tests.\n\nIt is not clear to me whether this is an issue only with my environment or instead this would affect the automated build/test within ONAP.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
